<br>
Next, you are playing an enchanter. What is being an enchanter like? Why did your character make the choice to follow the Path of Essence, instead of Harmony or Focus? How does he feel about his pets; are they mindless automatons bending to his will, willing servants brought from across the Veil for a time to aid him, wholly magical constructs crafted and shaped by your character, or something else entirely? How does he view magic, which is not only born into him but which he has made his life's work? Is it a tool to be used as needed, a living force with which he works, an inherent capacity in all beings, something else?<br>
<br>
Where was he born? Where did he grow up? Why does he adventure instead of being a safe merchant somewhere, or a scholar? What drives him to fight and struggle?<br>
<br>
You don't have to know all the answers to those questions before you start playing, of course. I usually don't know any. I tend to make characters and see how they turn out, what they seem to be like as I play them. But asking yourself questions about the realities of your character, the things you know, can help bring out the personality of that character.<br>
<br>
Good roleplayers, by the way and in my opinion, always accomodate others, so you shouldn't have to worry if your idea of a Lurikeen is different from someone else's. A good roleplayer will not be hampered by your interpretation; instead, they will be informed by yours, and hopefully you theirs, so that both of your ideas are expanded by contact with the other. That's really a large part of the fun of roleplaying for me; creating my own ideas, and then seeing what other people come up with.<br>
<br>
The best way to do it is just to try it. As you said, you don't want to talk like a guy sitting behind a computer. So, instead, try to talk like a Lurikeen enchanter, who has come across the Veil to aid the physical manifestation of his land in a battle against invaders and barbarians. Your ideas will mutate and change as you roleplay more, but that's fine. Just try to be that person for a little while, and see what happens. <p>Ailaen Grimeil<br>
Warrior-Poet<br>
